On 04/20/2011 07:33 AM, Muath wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Hi,
&gt; 1- I am wondering if there is a way to specify a seeds file for a job 
&gt; instead of filling out the textarea on the web interface. I have a 
&gt; seeds file with 100K URLs but I do not know how to provide it as input.
&gt;
In first you have to comment 2 beans and uncomment only one bean. The 2 
beans you have to comment them are as follows:

The first one
------------------

&lt;!--&lt;bean id=&quot;longerOverrides&quot; class=&quot;org.springframework.beans.factory.config.

   &lt;property name=&quot;properties&quot;&gt;

    &lt;props&gt;

     &lt;prop key=&quot;seeds.textSource.value&quot;&gt;

# URLS HERE

     &lt;/prop&gt;

    &lt;/props&gt;

   &lt;/property&gt;

  &lt;/bean&gt;  --&gt;

The second one
----------------------

&lt;!--&lt;bean id=&quot;seeds&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.seeds.TextSeedModule&quot;&gt;

      &lt;property name=&quot;textSource&quot;&gt;

       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.spring.ConfigString&quot;&gt;

        &lt;property name=&quot;value&quot;&gt;

         &lt;value&gt;

# [see override above]

         &lt;/value&gt;

        &lt;/property&gt;

       &lt;/bean&gt;

      &lt;/property&gt;

  &lt;property name=&#39;sourceTagSeeds&#39; value=&#39;false&#39;/&gt;

  &lt;/bean&gt;--&gt;

After that you have to uncomment the following bean:

  &lt;bean id=&quot;seeds&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.seeds.TextSeedModule&quot;&gt;

   &lt;property name=&quot;textSource&quot;&gt;

    &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.spring.ConfigFile&quot;&gt;

     &lt;property name=&quot;path&quot; value=&quot;seeds.txt&quot; /&gt;

    &lt;/bean&gt;

   &lt;/property&gt;

   &lt;property name=&#39;sourceTagSeeds&#39; value=&#39;false&#39;/&gt;

  &lt;/bean&gt;

Note that: I put seeds.txt in the same directory of Heritrix. You can 
put it under any directory as you want, but you have to write its path 
in the value as shown above.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; 2- Here is the scenarion I want to use Heritrix for and I would like 
&gt; to know if my assumptions are correct. I want to gather a data set 
&gt; consisting of webpages that have:
&gt; a- HTML forms
&gt; b- Javascript processing forms data.
&gt; Then I will go offline and iterate over the ARC archive files that 
&gt; result from my crawl using a java program. While iterating, I can 
&gt; check each one of the files if it is of type html/text and if so check 
&gt; if it contains an html form. If it does and the code that processes 
&gt; the form is in a separate javascript file is there a way to extract 
&gt; that file from the archives using for example its URL as an index or 
&gt; do I have to download that file again?
&gt;
I can&#39;t give you the correct answer.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; 3- Is there a good reference with some example profiles with values 
&gt; for the different configurations available along with description of 
&gt; when to use each of these profiles (I mean based on the bandwidth 
&gt; available to my machine and its processing power I can use these 
&gt; reference examples to better decide different inputs).
&gt;
You can look at this URL 
http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/6771. I hope 
it helps you.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Thanks for your help
&gt;
&gt; 

